    <h1 id="bkmrk-page-title" class="float left">Process - SNMP for Unifi AP</h1>

    <div style="clear:left;"></div>

            <p id="bkmrk-asummption%3A-telegraf">Assumption: Telegraf is already intalled and working</p>
<p id="bkmrk-%C2%A0"> </p>
<p id="bkmrk-in-unifi-manager-ena">In the Unifi wireless controller enable SNMP in settings, make note of the community string<br><a href="http://wiki/uploads/images/gallery/2017-12-Dec/SNMP_Community_String.png" target="_blank"><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="SNMP_Community_String.png"></a></p>
<p id="bkmrk-run-this-command-on-">Run these commands on the server monitoring SNMP</p>
<pre id="bkmrk-sudo-apt-get-install">sudo apt-get update<br>sudo apt-get install snmp snmp-mibs-downloader<br>sudo download-mib</pre>
<p id="bkmrk-additional-mib-libra">Additional MIB libraries are needed, place them in "/usr/share/snmp/mibs", wget the following links:</p>
<p id="bkmrk-https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Fp"><br><a href="https://github.com/pgmillon/observium/blob/master/mibs/FROGFOOT-RESOURCES-MIB">https://github.com/pgmillon/observium/blob/master/mibs/FROGFOOT-RESOURCES-MIB</a></p>
<pre id="bkmrk-frogfoot-resources-m"><code>FROGFOOT-RESOURCES-MIB

-- -*- mib -*-

DEFINITIONS ::= BEGIN

-- Frogfoot Networks CC Resources MIB

--
-- The idea behind this is to measure usage of resources.
-- It does not contain information about the system such as
